org.apache.hadoop.fs.contract

Class AbstractFSContract

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configured
      • org.apache.hadoop.fs.contract.AbstractFSContract
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Configurable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractBondedFSContract, LocalFSContract

    public abstract class AbstractFSContract
extends Configured
    Class representing a filesystem contract that a filesystem implementation is expected implement. Part of this contract class is to allow FS implementations to provide specific opt outs and limits, so that tests can be skip unsupported features (e.g. case sensitivity tests), dangerous operations (e.g. trying to delete the root directory), and limit filesize and other numeric variables for scale tests
